<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<ApexClass xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata">
    <apiVersion>49.0</apiVersion>
    <status>Active</status>
    <description>Apex controller for Lightning Web Component to edit student records</description>
    <userStory>As a user, I want to be able to edit Student records such as student name , student ID, student grade. using a Lightning Web Component and Apex class so that I can improve the user experience for my organization's Salesforce users. </userStory>
    <acceptanceCriteria>
        <criterion>The Lightning Web Component should use a lightning-record-edit-form to display the Student record fields such as student name , student ID, student grade.</criterion>
        <criterion>The Apex class should handle the record updates and perform any necessary validation.</criterion>
        <criterion>The user should be able to edit all fields on the Student record such as student name , student ID, student grade.</criterion>
        <criterion>Any validation errors should be displayed to the user in a clear and user-friendly manner.</criterion>
        <criterion>The Lightning Web Component and Apex class should adhere to Salesforce best practices and coding standards.</criterion>
    </acceptanceCriteria>
    <definitionOfDone>
        <step>The Lightning Web Component and Apex class should be developed and tested in a Salesforce sandbox or scratch org.</step>
        <step>The code should be thoroughly reviewed by at least one other developer.</step>
        <step>Automated tests should be written to ensure that the code works as expected and any potential issues are caught early.</step>
        <step>The code should be deployed to a production environment using a Salesforce change set or another deployment tool.</step>
        <step>The code should be documented, including any assumptions or constraints.</step>
        <step>The system administrator should be trained on how to use and maintain the new functionality.</step>
    </definitionOfDone>
</ApexClass>